article.headline: IUPUI 108, Oral Roberts 105 (3OT)
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Odell Bradley scored 41 points as IUPUI beat Oral Roberts 108-105 in a triple-overtime game Saturday night that featured 43 lead changes. Bradley broke his career scoring record two nights after scoring 32 in victory at Missouri-Kansas City in which he topped his previous personal best. IUPUI (12-6, 5-2 Mid-Continent) and Oral Roberts (13-6, 6-2) were tied at 35 at the half. The Golden Eagles lost despite shooting 53 percent from the field to the Jaguars' 49 percent. The teams both scored 18 points from the free throw line and had 42 rebounds, but IUPUI outscored Oral Roberts 30-27 from three-point range. The Jaguars also led in points off turnovers, 26-17. Caleb Green led Oral Roberts with 28 points on 10-for-14 shooting and grabbed a game-high 13 rebounds. The Golden Eagles also got 26 points from Ken Tutt, 21 from Jonathan Bluitt and 14 from Matt Gastel. Bradley finished 14-for-30, and hit 4-of-8 3-pointers. Akeem Clark scored 20 points for IUPUI and Matt Crenshaw had 18 on 7-for-11 shooting.
